**2. Nested Formatting Hell**
```
Text: "hello world"
Alice: Makes "hello" bold
Bob: Makes "o wo" italic

Result: "hell[o w]orld" needs to be bold+italic
Your system: ✅ Works (element can have multiple marks)

BUT:
Alice: Makes "hello" a link
Bob: Makes "o wo" a different link

Result: "hell[o w]orld" has TWO link marks
Your system: LWW means one link wins, the other disappears
Peritext: Defines mark splitting and priority rules
When Your System Breaks Down
Complex nested marks (links inside links, comments inside comments):

Peritext uses interval trees and mark priority
You'll need to add mark types (e.g., links can't nest, bold can stack)

